repository.corpname: Detroit Public Library. Burton Historical Collection.

physdesc.extent: (44 boxes, 1 large manuscript, 14 volumes, 1 film reel (16 mm), 3 film reels, (8 mm), 2 sound cassettes, 3 sound tape reels)

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into the following series: I. Background and history; II. Board of directors; III. Members; IV. Projects and programs; V. Public relations.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: Detroit Rotary began in 1910 with a membership of 15. By 1940 membership was over 400.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Papers, newsletters, correspondence and other materials. Formats include film and sound tapes, audio cassettes and slides.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Detroit Rotary Club papers, Burton Historical Collection, Detroit Public Library.

accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research use.

odd.head: General Note
odd.p: See finding aids for complete listing.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: This section includes not only description and background of the Rotary Club, but material concerning the Detroit club specifically, such as the building lease and insurance papers. It also includes guidelines and policies.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: The Board of Directors, supporting the Club President, manage the affairs of the Rotary Club. Included in this section are general correspondence, minutes of board meetings and reports.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Arranged alphabetically, the files on members include those people who either resigned from the Detroit club, died or were terminated. Also included in this series are directories and rosters. *Includes Obituary

odd.head: General note
odd.p: This series includes projects, programs, events and campaigns of the Detroit Rotary Club. Also placed in this series are Conferences and Conventions of Rotary International, plus Detroit Rotary Committees. Grants and Scholarships are also included here. (For information and files on the PolioPlus Campaign, see Committees.)

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Publicity, publications and general correspondence for the Detroit Rotary Club are contained in this series. Also included are miscellaneous audiotapes and sheet music.
